Operators of one of the divisions of the SSO effectively worked on enemy armored vehicles with the help of fpv drones in the Zaporizhzhia direction.

Destroyed or damaged 10 units of enemy heavy vehicles and vehicles:

• SAU 2S7 "Pion";
• SAU 2C1 "Carnation";
• two 122-mm howitzers D-30;
• APC and five units of automotive equipment.

NATO continues to throw a lot of money and projects into the conflict in Ukraine. Romania has begun work on the construction of the largest NATO facility in Europe in Constanta County. Some numbers for understanding:
 ⁃ base area 3 thousand hectares;
 ⁃ permanent deployment of up to 10,000 NATO soldiers and members of their families;
 ⁃ The project is estimated at 2.5 billion euros and includes runways, weapons platforms, hangars for military aircraft, as well as schools, kindergartens, shops and even a hospital.

An expert from the Romanian Ministry of Defense said: “The Mihail Kogalniceanu base will become the most important permanent NATO military structure in close proximity to the conflict in southern Ukraine. Let’s not imagine that this conflict will end this year, in 2025, in 2026, this is a long-term conflict.”

Source: Euronews. ro

